- Tree gofmt'ed — earlier milestones had misaligned fields (d49ca17)

## Key decisions (do not re-litigate without good reason)
- **State scope**: full history log (append-only) + current-state mirror for fast get_state
- **Lua concurrency**: one LState per script goroutine, never shared
- **Script registration**: in-script (ha.on_state_change style), no external manifest
- **KV encoding**: JSON round-trip via github.com/go-json-experiment/json (json/v2)
- **Global KV**: separate global_kv table (not a reserved script_id in script_kv); no proxy — use global.get/set directly
- **Timer IDs (every/at)**: stable key = script_id|type|spec|N; INSERT OR IGNORE preserves last_run/next_run across reloads
- **Timer IDs (after)**: UUID per call; row deleted after firing; orphaned rows cleaned up on startup
- **ha.after persistence**: best-effort — survives restart only if called at load time; callback-registered timers are dropped and logged on restart
- **Catch-up semantics**: fire at most once per missed timer (not replay all missed intervals)
- **Scheduler coupling**: scheduler sends TimerFiredEvent via onFire callback → script channel; scheduler does not hold *lua.LFunction references
- **HA add-on**: repo root = add-on directory; supervisor injects SUPERVISOR_TOKEN + ws://supervisor/core/websocket; scripts at /addon_config/scripts/; DB at /data/ha-lua.db; user options from /data/options.json
- **Config**: production reads /data/options.json; development uses --config flag pointing to config.dev.yaml
- **Lua sandbox**: SkipOpenLibs=true; open base/math/string/table/os/coroutine selectively; nil out load/loadfile/dofile/io/debug/package/os.execute/os.exit; replace require with restricted loader (scripts/lib/ only)
- **Error handling**: every callback dispatch wrapped in pcall; on error build exception info table {script_id, error, traceback, callback, event, timestamp} and call registered on_exception handler; slog.Error fallback if no handler; ha.exceptions.email uses net/smtp, ha.exceptions.log_file uses os.OpenFile append
- **JSON library**: github.com/go-json-experiment/json everywhere — deterministic key order, strict UTF-8; import path changes to encoding/json/v2 when stdlib proposal lands
- **Lua stdlib modules**: strings, time, json (v2), re (kept — user explicitly disagreed with cutting it), http, crypto (md5/sha1/sha256/sha512/hmac_sha256/hmac_sha512/base64/hex/rand/equal); math augmentation (round/clamp/log2/sign)
- **Tests**: real SQLite (:memory:) everywhere, no mocks; table-driven; helpers in internal/testutil/db.go
- **Benchmark regression**: benchstat comparison is informational only — bench-compare target prints output but does not fail the build; no cmd/bench-check tool
- **Purge**: single DELETE for rows older than retention_days (default 2); no downsampling; no stats tables; Purger.RunOnce() for tests
- **Retention config**: state_history.retention_days default 2; purge_interval default "1h"
- **Purge cutoff**: computed in Go as RFC3339 and bound as a parameter — never datetime('now',...) in SQL (format mismatch vs RFC3339 changed_at breaks string comparison)
- **Seed dedup**: state_history row on seed only when state/attributes differ from mirror (reconnects must not pollute history)
- **require semantics**: per-LState loaded-module cache + circular-require error (not bare DoFile)
- **http timeout**: callback context (5s) is the only timeout; no separate HTTP timeout config
- **Email cooldown**: per-script window (config.cooldown, default "15m"), suppressed errors counted and reported in next send; log_file is unlimited
- **ha.at timezone**: timezone config option → $TZ → UTC-with-warning; time/tzdata embedded; next_run stored UTC
- **Prod config channel**: /data/options.json + $SUPERVISOR_TOKEN only; run.sh passes no flags
- **golangci-lint**: v2 (config format version "2"); installed via release binary / official action, never go install

## Removed (do not add back without explicit user request)
- state_stats_hourly / state_stats_daily tables
- ha.get_stats
- is_numeric column on state_history
- 4-step transactional purge (aggregate → hourly → daily → delete)
- global.state() persistent-proxy (cache coherency issue with concurrent scripts)
- cmd/bench-check tool (over-engineered for a home project)

## User preferences observed
- Studio Code Server is the editor; scripts live at /config/ha-lua/scripts/
- Pure Go only — modernc.org/sqlite (no CGO), gopher-lua (no CGO)
- Deployment target: HA add-on (single static binary + /data + /addon_config volumes)
- Prefers planning to be done before any code is written
- Wants code written in the persona of Linus Torvalds; avoid needless complexity
